{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Grease 20 tart pans and set aside.","Place flour, baking powder, salt, butter, sugar, egg yolks and milk into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Wrap dough in cling wrap and refrigerate for 20 minutes.","Roll dough out between 2 pieces of cling wrap to ⅛-¼ inch thick. Cut 20 circles using a round cookie cutter (2½ in.). Place dough into tart pans and press into shape. Prick dough with a fork and place in freezer while preparing the filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in pecans. Reserve 20 pecan halves. Place remaining pecans into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add sugar, butter, maple syrup and eggs and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Fill chilled tarts with filling, garnish with reserved nuts and bake for 20-25 minutes (350°F). Allow to cool 5 minutes and while still hot brush tops with jelly. Cool completely before removing from tart pans. Serve immediately or store in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["2 ½ oz unsalted butter, chilled, cut into pieces, plus extra to grease","5 oz pastry flour","½ tsp baking powder","1 pinch salt","1 oz confectioners sugar","2 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 tbsp whole milk, chilled"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["7 oz pecan halves","2 oz soft dark brown sugar","2 oz unsalted butter, room temperature","4 oz maple syrup","2 large eggs","2 - 3 tbsp apple jelly              (optional)"]}],"id":"r164502","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-YH1q3nZf2zU\/XZWrGEWjuLI\/AAAAAAAAfiI\/osja06FQYMktyR0lGTklLsZlXOed4qbnQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_c3vdUZD0Uyaj-Ovs.png","title":"Pecan Pie Tarts","publishedAt":"2017-10-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"43 g","fat":"256 g","uom":"per 20 pieces","carbohydrates":"340 g","calories":"1556 kJ \/ 3718 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling wrap, round cookie cutter (2½ in.), rolling pin, small tart pans (approx. 1½ in. base), refrigerator, freezer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Dough should not be overworked. If dough becomes soft, place it in the refrigerator (approx. 15 min.) until it can be handled easily again.","Replace tart pans with a 12-hole cupcake pan. Grease generously with butter. Divide dough and roll out 12 circles (3¼ in.). Place pastry into each cupcake hole and press into shape. After tarts cool, run a small knife around edges of tarts to loosen for easy removal.","Place tarts back in the oven for 5 minutes to caramelize and set the jelly.","Replace pecan halves with pecan pieces.","Orange zest can be added to filling to intensify the flavor."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h 30m","2h 25m","20 pieces"]}